<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto w-full px-4 py-12 md:py-16">
	<h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-6">FAQ</h2>

	<div class="space-y-3">
		<details class="glass-clear rounded-xl group">
			<summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer text-sm font-medium text-foreground select-none list-none flex items-center justify-between">
				Is my data private?
				<span class="text-foreground-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">▾</span>
			</summary>
			<div class="px-6 pb-4 text-sm text-foreground-muted leading-relaxed">
				Yes. Recipe processes files entirely in your browser using WebAssembly.
				No files are uploaded to any server. No analytics, no tracking, no accounts.
				You can verify this by checking the Network tab in your browser's DevTools.
			</div>
		</details>

		<details class="glass-clear rounded-xl group">
			<summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer text-sm font-medium text-foreground select-none list-none flex items-center justify-between">
				Is Recipe legal?
				<span class="text-foreground-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">▾</span>
			</summary>
			<div class="px-6 pb-4 text-sm text-foreground-muted leading-relaxed">
				Recipe uses reverse-engineered file formats for interoperability, protected under
				DMCA Section 1201(f). Recipe is not affiliated with Nikon Corporation or Adobe Inc.
			</div>
		</details>
	</div>
</section>
